<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,500,1139]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Morphology. D VI + I,9–10; A I,9; P 13–16 (
<bibRefCitation author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Patzner, R. A." box="[704,969,536,563]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="95 - 102" refId="ref50197" refString="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (1995) A new species of Didogobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the western Mediterranean. Cybium, 19, 95 - 102." type="journal article" year="1995">Ahnelt &amp; Patzner 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Francour, P." box="[981,1151,536,563]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref54559" refString="Francour, P. (2008) First records of Didogobius splechtnai along the French Mediterranean coast and additional comments about D. schlieweni. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 38 (2), 139 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2008.38.2.09" type="journal article" year="2008">Francour 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Small goby with stocky body, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[220,798,572,598]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">large depressed head and a gently sloping snout.</emphasis>
Caudal peduncle deep, almost as deep as body. The first dorsal fin higher than the second, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,1202,608,634]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">its first spine longest, giving the fin a triangular shape.</emphasis>
Caudal fin rounded. Scales visible on body from reticulate pigmentation pattern along scale edges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,500,1139]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Body mostly dark brown with 3 moderately broad whitish to pale grayish bars extending onto ventral half of body, the first bar immediately in front of the first dorsal fin and extending onto ventral half of pectoral fins, plus a very thin one at the base of caudal fin</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[931,1014,752,778]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,1064,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-41@20.[151,1437,1064,1921]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Didogobius splechtnai. Photo by A. Pagano, Sicily, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601607/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). First dorsal fin colored like adjacent body, with scattered white flecks and streaks, outer membrane between first two spines white (
<bibRefCitation author="Louisy, P." box="[1197,1342,788,815]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Patzner, R. A." pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,500,1139]" box="[199,648,860,887]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bath" authorityYear="1971" box="[383,641,860,886]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gammogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steinitzi">
<emphasis box="[383,641,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Gammogobius steinitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,500,1139]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Habitat. Infralittoral to circalittoral species, known from depth of 
<quantity box="[926,1013,896,923]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="30.0" valueMax="56.0" valueMin="4.0">
4– 
<specimenCount box="[954,1013,896,923]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="generic">56 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Present in small cavities in innermost parts of large marine caves and in small bottom caves and cavities. Mostly found lying on the soft sediment in recesses, ready to dive into a nearby hole or crevice (summarized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Francour, P." box="[925,1094,968,995]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref54559" refString="Francour, P. (2008) First records of Didogobius splechtnai along the French Mediterranean coast and additional comments about D. schlieweni. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 38 (2), 139 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2008.38.2.09" type="journal article" year="2008">Francour 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,500,1139]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean, there are records from the northwestern Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Patzner, R. A." pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="95 - 102" refId="ref50197" refString="Ahnelt, H. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (1995) A new species of Didogobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the western Mediterranean. Cybium, 19, 95 - 102." type="journal article" year="1995">Ahnelt &amp; Patzner 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Francour, P." box="[311,477,1040,1067]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref54559" refString="Francour, P. (2008) First records of Didogobius splechtnai along the French Mediterranean coast and additional comments about D. schlieweni. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 38 (2), 139 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2008.38.2.09" type="journal article" year="2008">Francour 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Iglesias, S. P. &amp; Bariche, M. &amp; Beau, F. &amp; Berenger, L. &amp; Beucher, R. &amp; Chabrolle, A. &amp; Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Cousin, B. &amp; Curd, A. &amp; Danet, V. &amp; Duhamel, E. &amp; Duval, A. &amp; Farque, P. A. &amp; Goascoz, N. &amp; Jadaud, A. &amp; Larnaud, P. &amp; Le Bouter, M. &amp; Le Bras, Y. &amp; Le Bris, S. &amp; Lombard, L. &amp; Louisy, P. &amp; Mandine, M. &amp; Mas, L. &amp; Menut, T. &amp; Metral, L. &amp; Poussard, P. &amp; Quero, J. C. &amp; Raybaud, V. &amp; Renoult, J. P. &amp; Richard, T. &amp; Spitz, J. &amp; Ternon, Q. &amp; Thiriet, P. &amp; Tournier-Broer, R." box="[488,715,1040,1067]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="169 - 188" refId="ref56818" refString="Iglesias, S. P., Bariche, M., Beau, F., Berenger, L., Beucher, R., Chabrolle, A., Cottalorda, J. M., Cousin, B., Curd, A., Danet, V., Duhamel, E., Duval, A., Farque, P. A., Goascoz, N., Jadaud, A., Larnaud, P., Le Bouter, M., Le Bras, Y., Le Bris, S., Lombard, L., Louisy, P., Mandine, M., Mas, L., Menut, T., Metral, L., Poussard, P., Quero, J. C., Raybaud, V., Renoult, J. P., Richard, T., Spitz, J., Ternon, Q., Thiriet, P. &amp; Tournier-Broer, R. (2021 b) French Ichthyological Records for 2019. Cybium, 45 (3), 169 - 188. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2020 - 444 - 001" type="journal article" year="2021">
Iglésias 
<emphasis box="[580,628,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2021b
</bibRefCitation>
), Lampedusa (Stefanni 1999) and Adriatic Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Herler, J. &amp; Patzner, R. A." pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="153 - 155" refId="ref56046" refString="Herler, J. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (2002) New records of Didogobius splechtnai Ahnelt &amp; Patzner, 1955 (Pisces: Gobiidae) from the Tyrrhenian and northern Adriatic Sea. Cybium, 26, 153 - 155." type="journal article" year="2002">Herler &amp; Patzner 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M." box="[226,392,1076,1103]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref57897" refString="Kovacic, M. (2005) An annotated checklist of the family Gobiidae in the Adriatic Sea. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 15, 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2005">Kovačić 2005</bibRefCitation>
). A record from 
<collectingCountry box="[590,671,1076,1102]" name="Turkey" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, Aegean Sea (Francour 
<emphasis box="[955,1008,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2007), seems probable but was not substantiated by specimens or photos, later confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ragkousis, M. &amp; Digenis, M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Katsanevakis, S. &amp; Gerovasileiou, V." box="[796,1057,1112,1139]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="557" refId="ref63299" refString="Ragkousis, M., Digenis, M., Kovacic, M., Katsanevakis, S. &amp; Gerovasileiou, V. (2021) Rarely reported cryptobenthic fish in marine caves of the Eastern Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Marine Science and Engeneering, 9, 557. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / jmse 9060557" type="journal article" year="2021">
Ragkousis 
<emphasis box="[919,969,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
for Aegean Sea.
</paragraph>
